            "SummaryExplanation": {
                "val": "The $620.417 million increase is driven in support of the fielding of an experimental prototype with residual combat capability . The program plans on executing and accelerating the building and delivery of Long Range Hypersonic Weapon, Common Hypersonic Glide Body (CHGB) prototypes, and 34.5 inch Missile Body booster prototypes.  Additionally, prototyping of Thermal Protection System (TPS) for the glide bodies will be stood up to expand the industrial base of TPS suppliers."
            }
